## Summary

### What worked out of the box
- Django ASGI setup, Channels + `AuthMiddlewareStack` + `AllowedHostsOriginValidator` wiring
- `django-tasks-rq` вЂ” once the correct module path was identified
- MinIO + Redis + Postgres Docker healthchecks and `--wait`
- `EchoConsumer` WebSocket round-trip
- `MediaController` POST with msgspec validation (201 on valid, 400 on missing field)
- `/healthz` and `/readyz` endpoints
- `structlog` pretty-dev logging with `request_id` middleware

### What broke / required fixes

| Issue | Fix |
|---|---|
| `django_tasks_rq.backends.RQBackend` вЂ” wrong module path | Changed to `django_tasks_rq.backend.RQBackend` (no `s`) |
| `django-modern-rest` imports `jwt` unconditionally even without JWT auth | Added `pyjwt` as a dependency |
| `django_rq` not in `INSTALLED_APPS` | Added `"django_rq"` to `THIRD_PARTY_APPS` |
| Port 5432 already in use (host Postgres) | Changed docker-compose host port to `5433` |
| `djangoSettingsModule` in `[tool.pyright]` is unrecognized | Removed вЂ” belongs only in `[tool.django-stubs]` |
| `channels` `as_asgi()` return type incompatible with Django `path()` | Added `# type: ignore[arg-type]` |
| Smoke tests hit stale 03-jobs-board `runserver` on port 8000 | Killed the stale process; smoke rule: `pkill` old servers before starting new ones |

### Suggested skill changes

1. **`django_tasks_rq` backend path**: Document that the correct dotted path is `django_tasks_rq.backend.RQBackend` (singular `backend`, not `backends`).
2. **`pyjwt` implicit dependency**: `django-modern-rest` requires `pyjwt` even when JWT auth is not used. Add it as an implicit dep whenever `django-modern-rest` is included.
3. **`django_rq` in `INSTALLED_APPS`**: When adding `django-tasks-rq`, also add `"django_rq"` to `INSTALLED_APPS` вЂ” it ships migrations.
4. **Port conflict guard**: Before starting uvicorn in smoke checks, add `pkill -f uvicorn || true` (or kill by PID file) to clear stale servers from prior runs.
5. **`[tool.pyright]` vs `[tool.django-stubs]`**: `djangoSettingsModule` belongs only in `[tool.django-stubs]`, not `[tool.pyright]`.
